querySelector() selects the value just like css and helps in dom modification
.textContent can be used as a getter and setter--getter to write the value 
                                         getter-- to read the value
also textContent can only be used for text stting and not HTML tag setting.

document.querySelector().innerHTML = '<b> some text </b>'
--->some text in bold
document.querySelector().textContent = '<b> some text </b>';
--->'<b> some text </b>'

